# Vue 3 Debugging Guide

## Reactivity Not Working

### Problem
Data changes but UI doesn't update.

### Solutions
```typescript
// BAD: Replacing reactive object
let state = reactive({ count: 0 })
state = reactive({ count: 1 })  // Lost reactivity!

// GOOD: Mutate properties
const state = reactive({ count: 0 })
state.count = 1  // Works!

// BAD: Destructuring reactive
const { count } = reactive({ count: 0 })  // count is not reactive!

// GOOD: Use toRefs
const state = reactive({ count: 0 })
const { count } = toRefs(state)  // count.value is reactive

// BAD: ref without .value in script
const count = ref(0)
count = 1  // Wrong!

// GOOD: Use .value
count.value = 1  // Correct
```

## Watch Not Triggering

```typescript
// BAD: Watching reactive object property directly
const state = reactive({ user: { name: 'John' } })
watch(state.user, () => {})  // Won't trigger on nested changes

// GOOD: Use getter or deep watch
watch(() => state.user, () => {}, { deep: true })
watch(() => state.user.name, (newName) => {})

// BAD: Watching ref without callback
watch(count.value, () => {})  // Watching primitive!

// GOOD: Watch the ref itself
watch(count, (newVal) => {})
```

## Pinia Store Issues

```typescript
// BAD: Destructuring store loses reactivity
const { user } = useAuthStore()  // Not reactive!

// GOOD: Use storeToRefs
import { storeToRefs } from 'pinia'
const store = useAuthStore()
const { user } = storeToRefs(store)  // Reactive!

// Actions can be destructured directly
const { login, logout } = useAuthStore()  // OK
```
